%description
An implementation of the stratification index proposed by Zhou (2012)
<DOI:10.1177/0081175012452207>. The package provides two functions, srank,
which returns stratum-specific information, including population share and
average percentile rank; and strat, which returns the stratification index
and its approximate standard error. When a grouping factor is specified,
strat also provides a detailed decomposition of the overall stratification
into between-group and within-group components.

